  <summary>7/14/1987--Introduced.
Amends Federal law relating to the policing of the buildings and grounds of the Library of Congress to authorize the Librarian of Congress to designate certain employees as police (rather than as special police). Provides that the rank structure and pay for such police shall be the same as that for the Capitol Police.</summary>
